result.execSummary:
The defendant Robert L Trammell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Robert L Trammell is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Robert L Trammell was found guilty of Receiving Stolen Property (>$10,000) [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.34(1)(c).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to: Fond du lac case 13CF449; Waukesha case 14CF660; Walworth case 14CF316

superMiscConds.notes: Fines, costs, and restitution are due during term of supervision.  Dept of Corrections to collect from defendant's wages and from other monies held in the defendant's inmate account, an amount or a percentage which the department determines is reasonable.  If defendant is released with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment enforceable by all creditors' remedies shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.

Any counseling deemed appropriate by department.
Maintain full time employment and/or schooling.
Not allowed on car dealership lots.
No contact with 5 Corners Dodge located in Cedarburg WI.
  Absolute sobriety.  No possession/consumption of any intoxicants.
Submit to DNA sample forthwith.
Be booked for ATN #
